le=\"font-size:smaller\"| [[2012\u20132013 United States network television schedule|2012-2013]]\n! style=\"background:#fc9;\"|#147\n! style=\"background:#fc9;\" |0.77<ref name=\"Spotted2012\">{{cite web|url=http://www.spottedratings.com/2012/10/spotvault-90210-cw-2012-13-ratings.html?m=1 |title=SpotVault - 90210 (CW) - 2012-13 Ratings |date=October 14, 2012 |website=Spotted Ratings}}</ref>\n! style=\"background:#fc9;\" |0.4<ref name=\"Spotted2012\"/>\n|}\n\nThe series premiere was seen by 4.65&nbsp;million U.S. viewers.<ref>[https://archive.today/20120721070509/http://tvbythenumbers.com/2008/09/10/top-cw-primetime-shows-september-1-7/5026 Top CW primetime shows September 1-7]. Retrieved: October 13, 2010.</ref> The UK premiere was seen by 468,000 viewers on [[E4 (TV channel)|E4]].<ref name=\"BARB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/weekly-top-10/?|title=UK Television viewing figures (Choose relevant dates)|work=Barb|accessdate=March 10, 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe second season premiered to 2.56 million viewers and achieved 1.3 rating in the Adults 18-49 demographic, up 18% from its first-season finale but down 50% from its series premiere.<ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.com/2009/09/09/tv-ratings-tuesday-90210-melrose-place-premiere-weak-fox-hells-kitchen-rule-the-night/26542 TV Ratings Tuesday: 90210, Melrose Place Premiere Weak; Fox & Hell's Kitchen Rule]. Retrieved: October 13, 2010.</ref> Although ratings decreased after its three-month hiatus it was the #1 most successful show on DVR in the 18-49 percentage increase between March 22\u201328 increasing to a 1.1 rating.<ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/04/12/greys-anatomy-big-bang-theory-90210-are-dvr-viewing-standouts/48089 Greys Anatomy, Big Band Theory and 90210 are DVR viewing standouts]. Retrieved: April 21, 2010.</ref> DVR ratings for the show have sometimes doubled its broadcast ratings.<ref name=\"DVR Dawn\">[http://www.tvfanatic.com/2010/03/cw-president-teases-the-vampire-diaries-spin-off/ CW president teases The Vampire Diaries spin-off]. Retrieved: October 25, 2010.</ref><ref name=\"DVR 90210\">[http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/04/12/vampire-diaries-and-top-model-each-add-over-1-million-viewers-with-all-dvr-playback-factored-in/48081 90210 DVR ratings]. Retrieved: April 21, 2010.</ref> The CW have described its DVR ratings as some of the most impressive on TV and cited them as the reason for the series' fourth season renewal.<ref name=\"Early renewals The CW 2011-12\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/04/26/%E2%80%9Cthe-vampire-diaries%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9Cgossip-girl%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9C90210%E2%80%9D-%E2%80%9Csupernatural%E2%80%9D-americas-next-top-model-renewed-by-the-cw/90700/comment-page-4#comment-819642|title=\"The Vampire Diaries,\" \"Gossip Girl,\" \"90210,\" \"Supernatural\" & \"America's Next Top Model\" Renewed By The CW|last=Gorman|first=Bill|date=April 26, 2011|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=April 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe third-season premiere was viewed by 1.96&nbsp;million viewers in the United States and achieved a 0.9 rating in Adults 18-49.<ref name=\"belles\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bourgy.com/wordpress/2010/09/14/ratings-vma-awards-dominates-all/ |title=Ratings: VMA Awards Dominates All |author=Matic |date=September 14, 2010 |work=Bourgy |accessdate=December 3, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314075759/http://www.bourgy.com/wordpress/2010/09/14/ratings-vma-awards-dominates-all/ |archivedate=March 14, 2012 }}</ref> Episode 11 hit season highs in all categories with a 1.1 Adults 18-49 rating, 1.4 Adults 18-34 and 2.1 in The CW's target of Women 18-34. It was also the most watched episode in over a year with 2.18&nbsp;million viewers tuning in.<ref name=\"90210 season 3 highs\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2010/12/07/monday-final-ratings-hawaii-five-0-90210-adjusted-up-skating-with-the-stars-castle-2-5-men-down/74654|first=Bill|last=Gorman|title=Monday Final Ratings: 'Hawaii Five-0,' '90210,' '2.5 Men' Adjusted Up; 'Skating With The Stars,' 'Castle' Down|date=December 7, 2010|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=December 7, 2010}}</ref> In the UK, the eighth episode of season three \"Mother Dearest\" was seen by 548,000 viewers, bettering its series premiere.<ref name=\"BARB\" />\n\n===Critical response===\nMost reviews of the pilot were average. [[Metacritic]] gave the episode a Metascore\u2014a weighted average based on the impressions of a select 12 critical reviews\u2014of 46, signifying mixed or average reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/shows/90210|title=''90210'' (CW)|accessdate=January 29, 2009|website=[[Metacritic]]| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090202122114/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/shows/90210| archivedate=February 2, 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref> Matthew Gilbert of ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' felt that like the original, ''90210'' was \"pretty good\". Gilbert said that the episode \"seemed to take forever to set up some remarkably bland plotlines\", which he found had been executed with more finesse by other teen soaps. The reviewer criticized the writers for \"unimaginative material\", and commented on the risqu\u00e9 oral sex scene. Gilbert claimed that the characters lacked depth and distinction throughout the pilot, especially Naomi, whom he compared negatively to ''[[Gossip Girl (TV series)|Gossip Girl]]''{{'}}s [[Blair Waldorf]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/tv/blog/2008/09/review_9021eww.html|title=Review: 9021-Eww|accessdate=January 30, 2009|author=Gilbert, Matthew|date=September 2, 2008|work=The Boston Globe | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090202031814/http://www.boston.com/ae/tv/blog/2008/09/review_9021eww.html| archivedate=February 2, 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref> By contrast, Tom Gliatto of ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine gave Naomi Clark a favorable review, but stated that he felt the cast as a whole had yet to gel.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Tom |last=Gliatto |title=''90210'' Review:The New Kids Have Yet To 'Gel' |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=September 3, 2008 |accessdate=November 21, 2019 |url=https://people.com/tv/90210-review-the-new-kids-have-yet-to-gel/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090420210152/http://tvwatch.people.com/2008/09/03/90210-review-the-new-kids-have-yet-to-gel/ |archivedate=April 20, 2009 }}</ref> When compared to the original series, Rob Owen of the ''[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]'' felt that the spin-off covered the same themes\u2014family, friends, teen melodrama, relationships\u2014but with more humor. Owen praised the compelling characters and the acting, and found the dialogue to be more painful than clever.<ref name=\"robreview\">{{cite web|url=http://community.post-gazette.com/blogs/tunedin/archive/2008/09/02/90210-premieres.aspx |title=''90210'' premieres |accessdate=January 30, 2009 |author=Owen, Rob |date=September 2, 2008 |work=[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090202183417/http://community.post-gazette.com/blogs/tunedin/archive/2008/09/02/90210-premieres.aspx |archivedate=February 2, 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nAs the show continued its first season, the response became considerably more positive, and by the second season critical response was favorable. ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the second season an A-, stating that \"all it took was a little sunshine to give this show some heat\", and that the \"new, trashier take is working\" after what they considered a \"drippy\" first season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/ew/tv/tonights_best_tv/0,,2,00.html |title=Tonight's Best &#124; TV|work=Entertainment Weekly |date=September 12, 2009}}</ref> LaDale Anderson of ''[[Canyon News]]'' commented on the change between the first two seasons, saying that \"the transformation of the characters and storylines in season two has been fantastic\", and \"sometimes a show needs a makeover and with the right pieces in place a not so good show can become something sensational.\" The reviewer opined that \"what has worked so well [...] is that the characters are not one-dimensional. With most shows characters seamlessly continue to embody characteristics that solely define them, but not here.\" Anderson also praised the writing, saying it was \"intricate and intertwines itself without forcing the storylines to connect; they mesh naturally.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.canyon-news.com/artman2/publish/Television/90210_is_a_guilty_pleasure_that_delivers_multi-layered_characters_and_storylines.php |title=''90210'' Is A Guilty Pleasure That Delivers |author=Anderson, LaDale |date=December 10, 2009 |work=[[Canyon News]] |accessdate=December 10, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716185317/http://www.canyon-news.com/artman2/publish/Television/90210_is_a_guilty_pleasure_that_delivers_multi-layered_characters_and_storylines.php |archivedate=July 16, 2011 }}</ref>\n\n===Awards and accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|+ Awards and accolades for ''90210''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipients and nominees\n! Outcome\n|-\n|rowspan=\"10\"|2009\n|[[People's Choice Award]]\n|Favorite New TV Drama\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''90210''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Prism Awards]]\n|Drama Series Multi-Episode Storyline\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Performance in a Drama Multi-Episode Storyline\n|[[Jessica Lowndes]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice Drama Series|Choice TV Drama]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''90210''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice Breakout Series|TV Breakout Show]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Choice TV Actor\n|[[Dustin Milligan]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|TV Breakout Female\n|[[AnnaLynne McCord]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|TV Breakout Star\n|[[Tristan Wilds]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|TV Parental Unit\n|[[Rob Estes]] and [[Lori Loughlin]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[ASCAP Award]]\n|Top Television Serie